HEADWORD: Winglet
<hw>Wing"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A little
wing; a very small wing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A bastard wing, or
alula.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wingmanship</ent>⟦br⟧
